title: Fire Island National Seashore: Photo Gallery
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Photos & Multimedia     Photo Gallery               Photo Gallery                    Fire Island Wilderness   3 Photos  Views of the Otis Pike Fire Island High Dune Wilderness.          A Tour of the Sunken Forest   5 Photos  Photographic Tour of the Sunken Forest          Watch Hill Nature Trail, Early Fall   6 Photos  Images from the boardwalk trail through the salt marsh and dunes at Watch Hill.            Volunteers Make a Difference   6 Photos  Volunteers-In-Parks ("VIPs") work side-by-side with National Park Service employees and partners to help care for America's national parks.          Protecting Piping Plovers on Fire Island   8 Photos  This tiny and threatened shorebird nests on Fire Island's beaches. Park staff, volunteers, and Fire Island residents work together to protect Piping Plovers.          Beach Dynamics   8 Photos  On the beach, no two days are alike. Wind and waves carry sand to and from our shores, constantly changing the shape of the shoreline.
